Rationale1: Idiomatic Kotlin
Decision2: Make the `<method_name>` return full working connections
Rationale2: Previously the returned connections required the caller to do extra work: setting up tunnels and performing an `<iden>` handshake. With this change, we make a complete working connection in `<method_name>`. This will make it easier to fix fallback when a single domain has multiple `<iden>` addresses that are not reachable. Also, this will make it easier to do SPDY through `<iden>` proxies.

Decision2: Make the `<method_name>` return full working connections
Rationale2: Previously the returned connections required the caller to do extra work: setting up tunnels and performing an `<iden>` handshake. With this change, we make a complete working connection in `<method_name>`. This will make it easier to fix fallback when a single domain has multiple `<iden>` addresses that are not reachable. Also, this will make it easier to do SPDY through `<iden>` proxies.

Rationale2: Previously the returned connections required the caller to do extra work: setting up tunnels and performing an `<iden>` handshake. Also, this will make it easier to do SPDY through `<iden>` proxies.

Rationale1: Java 9
Decision2: Make the `<method_name>` return full working connections
Rationale2: Previously the returned connections required the caller to do extra work: setting up tunnels and performing an `<iden>` handshake. With this change, we make a complete working connection in `<method_name>`. This will make it easier to fix fallback when a single domain has multiple `<iden>` addresses that are not reachable. Also, this will make it easier to do SPDY through `<iden>` proxies.

Rationale2: Previously the returned connections required the caller to do extra work: setting up tunnels and performing an `<iden>` handshake. With this change, we make a complete working connection in `<method_name>`. This will make it easier to fix fallback when a single domain has multiple `<iden>` addresses that are not reachable. Also, this will make it easier to do SPDY through `<iden>` proxies.

Rationale1: I prefer signed
Decision2: Make the `<method_name>` return full working connections
Rationale2: Previously the returned connections required the caller to do extra work: setting up tunnels and performing an `<iden>` handshake. With this change, we make a complete working connection in `<method_name>`. This will make it easier to fix fallback when a single domain has multiple `<iden>` addresses that are not reachable. Also, this will make it easier to do SPDY through `<iden>` proxies.

Decision2: Make the `<method_name>` return full working connections
Rationale2: Previously the returned connections required the caller to do extra work: setting up tunnels and performing an `<iden>` handshake. With this change, we make a complete working connection in `<method_name>`. This will make it easier to fix fallback when a single domain has multiple `<iden>` addresses that are not reachable. Also, this will make it easier to do SPDY through `<iden>` proxies.

Decision2: Make the `<method_name>` return full working connections
Rationale2: Previously the returned connections required the caller to do extra work: setting up tunnels and performing an `<iden>` handshake. Also, this will make it easier to do SPDY through `<iden>` proxies.

Decision1: Fix <iden> post retransmit in the new API

Decision2: Make the `<method_name>` return full working connections
Rationale2: Previously the returned connections required the caller to do extra work: setting up tunnels and performing an `<iden>` handshake. Also, this will make it easier to do SPDY through `<iden>` proxies.

Decision1: Add some pings to force happens-before in <iden> tests
Rationale1: Previously we were relying on accidents to get our tests to pass
Decision2: Make the `<method_name>` return full working connections
Rationale2: Previously the returned connections required the caller to do extra work: setting up tunnels and performing an `<iden>` handshake. With this change, we make a complete working connection in `<method_name>`. This will make it easier to fix fallback when a single domain has multiple `<iden>` addresses that are not reachable. Also, this will make it easier to do SPDY through `<iden>` proxies.

Decision1: Introduce a <file_name> interface between engine and connection.
Rationale1: This breaks the direct dependency from <file_name> to <method_name>
Decision2: Make the `<method_name>` return full working connections
Rationale2: Previously the returned connections required the caller to do extra work: setting up tunnels and performing an `<iden>` handshake. With this change, we make a complete working connection in `<method_name>`. This will make it easier to fix fallback when a single domain has multiple `<iden>` addresses that are not reachable. Also, this will make it easier to do SPDY through `<iden>` proxies.

Rationale1: Previously the returned connections required the caller to do extra work: setting up tunnels and performing an `<iden>` handshake. Also, this will make it easier to do SPDY through `<iden>` proxies.
